ğŸ” Findings
Active user sessions were identified both locally and remotely
Open shared files revealed live data access
Network connections exposed running services and potential attacker activity
Python script provided real-time network usage metrics

ğŸ“š Lessons Learned
Volatile data must be collected first during incident response
Live systems contain critical evidence that disappears after shutdown
Combining native commands with forensic tools improves visibility
